        "comment": "On a clear night, the surface of the snowpack will thinly freeze. It will soon dry out in the morning and remain soft into the night.\nSunny slopes are already quite dry even in the high alpine regions.\n\nIn the old snow cover, the snow layers are mostly well connected. More or less deep below the surface, there are several weak layers of faceted snow crystals and discontinuous grains, which are more frequent on the axial slopes above 1800 m."
